Introduction

MY.st (Korean: 마이스트; Japanese: マイストゥ) was a five-member boy group under MYstar Entertainment and MY Entertainment. They first debuted in Japan on August 12, 2018 with the mini album Boy N Girl and made their Korean debut on March 26, 2020 with the mini album The Glow : Eden.

On July 17, 2021, Kim Keonwoo revealed through his Instagram that the group had disbanded due various reasons including their agency's financial and credit problems.
